  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "UI/UX Designer (HCI)",
  "description": "<p>As a UI/UX Designer, you will shape end-to-end user experiences by uncovering user needs, designing intuitive journeys, and delivering engaging interfaces. <u><strong>Please attach a copy of, or link to your portfolio for this application.</strong></u><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct user research (interviews, observations, usability testing) to identify insights and pain points</li><li>Translate insights into user journeys, wireframes, prototypes, and high-quality UI designs</li><li>Design intuitive, accessible, and visually compelling digital interfaces</li><li>Facilitate design thinking workshops, ideation sessions, and problem-framing activities</li><li>Collaborate cross-functionally to define problems, co-create solutions, and iterate quickly</li><li>Explore and apply new tools, technologies, and design methods to improve outcomes</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Design, HCI, or a related field (or equivalent practical experience)</li><li>At least <strong>5 years of hands-on UI/UX experience</strong>, including user research and UI design</li><li>Strong portfolio demonstrating user-centered design and problem-solving skills</li><li>Experience facilitating workshops and working with non-design stakeholders</li><li>Familiarity with Agile environments and iterative product development</li><li>Proficiency in tools such as <strong>Figma, Miro</strong>, and user research/testing platforms</li><li>Working knowledge of <strong>HTML/CSS</strong> (JavaScript is a plus)</li><li>Strong analytical, communication, storytelling, and collaboration skills</li><li>Ownership of complex, multi-stakeholder initiatives</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
